THOUGHT: Now I need to add the `checkstyle` configuration block to `app/build.gradle`. This block will define the Checkstyle tool version, the path to the ruleset file (which I'll create later), and the source sets to be analyzed. I'll place this block at the end of the `app/build.gradle` file.

```bash
cat <<'EOF' >> app/build.gradle

checkstyle {
    toolVersion = checkstyle.version
    configFile = rootProject.file('config/checkstyle/checkstyle.xml')
    sourceSets = [project.sourceSets.main]
}

tasks.withType(Checkstyle) {
    reports {
        xml.required = true
        html.required = true
    }
}
EOF
```

